 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search This job has expired on Indeed Reasons could include: the employer is not accepting applications, is not actively hiring, or is reviewing applications Contracts Counsel NICE inContact Salt Lake City, UT Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Contracts Counsel 
Location: Salt Lake City, UT 
The Contracts Counsel is responsible for negotiations of favorable terms, pricing, and conditions of contracts. Serve as subject matter expert in the area of contract negotiation. Draft contracts and review customer or business partner contract language for appropriateness and compliance with organizational policies and governmental regulations. This position also provides advice and counsel regarding legal requirements, best practices, and strategies for managing risk in order to avoid litigation.
 
 
 As a Contracts Counsel, a Typical Day Might Include the Following: 
 
Review and administer contracts. 
Analyze and assist in contract negotiations and manage approval process. 
Communicate with internal departments to coordinate contract reviews and approvals. 
Analyze change requests to existing contracts and approve changes or revisions. 
Draft contract language. 
Ensure that contract provisions are clear and conform to company policies, contract law and applicable regulations. 
Identify and report potential risk associated with customer facing contracts. 
Assist in assessment of customer and corporate risk. 
Obtaining appropriate signature for all contracts. 
Manage NICE inContact's product Standard Terms of Use to comply with business and legal requirements 
Draft ad hoc contracts and agreements utilized by the company (except Human Resource documents) 
Coordinate with Corporate Counsel in all litigation matters & trademark filings. 
 
 To Land This Gig You'll Need: 
 
Juris Doctorate Degree 
5-8 years post graduate experience in contract negotiation. 
Experience in reviewing, drafting, and tracking contracts 
Ability to identify problems and engage others towards solution 
Ability to meet deadlines 
Analytical skills are a must 
 
Bonus Experience: 
 
3-5 years in negotiation of information technology sales, supplier and business partner agreements. 
Experience with privacy regulation including GDPR 
Experience handling dispute resolution with customers and vendors 
Previous sales experience 
 
